olive oil
1 ciabatta
1 packet prosciutto
½ packet Rocket leaves
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Beetroot Relish
½ packet goat cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Slice ciabatta widthways into 1cm-thick slices.
• Divide ciabatta slices in a single layer between two lined oven trays and drizzle generously with olive oil. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Bake until golden and crisp, 3-4 minutes. Allow to cool.

• Tear or slice prosciutto into small pieces.
• In a medium bowl, combine rocket leaves (see ingredients) and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Top toasts with beetroot relish, balsamic rocket, prosciutto and crumbled goat cheese (see ingredients).

• Arrange prosciutto-loaded toasts on serving platters.
• Serve with any remaining balsamic rocket. Enjoy!